@node Intro "Introduction"
Introduction

StartDia is an Amiga utility, intended to provide users of Alexander
Pratch Dia program with an alternative User Interface. Not that I am
implying Alexander's UI is bad. :-) Only I found that it missed some
features I'd like. And since Alexander is busy on PicoPainter etc. I
decided to use Dias ARexx port to write my own User Interface to it.

Which provides the following features.

- Fully Style Guide compliant.

- Uses the ScreenMode requester. Allowing you to select a screenmode  
  for Dia. (User's of 2.0 may want to use the ReqTools.library as in
  2.04 ASL does not provide a ScreenMode requester. ReqTools does.

- Uses the File requester to help you to select the picture/anim you
  wish to play.

- Rx option will give you a ListView window with most of Dia's ARexx
  commands. As well as an 'RX' command allowing you to run any ARexx
  script for talking to Dia. Also allowing for user parameters to be
  adedd to the selected ARexx commands.

- Selectable Screendepth. Current setting is used upon starting Dia.

- AutoClear.  (Automatically clear screen when loading next picture)
  on/off switch. Current setting is used upon starting Dia.  And can
  also be set from the Rx command.

- Zoom Window (Iconify Dia's command window) option that's used upon
  starting Dia.

- Program settings,(Dia Path, ScreenMode/Autoclear/Zoom/ScreenDepth)
  can be saved and loaded.  When a config file is present it will be
  loaded when Dia is started.

- When a new ScreenMode is selected StartDia will automatically quit
  a running Dia and restart it in the selected mode.

- When selecting the RX command Dia will automatically be started.

- Dia can be started and quit from within StartDia. There is no need
  to manually start or quit Dia when using StartDia.

- Pleasingly styled look. ;-) Using as little resources as possible.

- Automatically centers itself on the screen.
 
@endnode Intro

@node Using "Using StartDia"
Using StartDia

The command synopsis for StartDia is:

CLI: StartDia
WB : click on the StartDia icon. 

After running StartDia a window is opened where you can control Dia.
Said window looks roughly like the ASCII representation below.

     +-+------------------------------------------------+--+--+ 
     |o| @{"Dia Starter V1.0" Link Intro }       @{"Menu's" Link Menu }                 |  |  |
     +--------------------------------------------------------+
     | +------------------ Dia ToolTypes -------------------+ | 
     | |                                                    | |
     | |  @{"Screen " Link SB }  @{" PICOa:EGS 1024x768                " Link ST } @{"?" Link QB }   | |
     | |                                                    | |
     | |  @{"File   " Link FB }  @{" PICS:JPEG/MyPicture.JPG              " Link FT }  | |
     | |                                                    | |
     | |  @{"DiaPath" Link PB }  @{" EGS:Piccolo/Dia/Dia              " Link PT }  @{"Rx" Link RB }  | |
     | |                                                    | |
     | |    @{"Depth" Link DC }             @{"Zoom" Link ZC }          @{"AutoClear" Link AC }      | |
     | | +-------------+  +------------+  +---------------+ | |
     | | |@|   16      |  |@|  Off     |  |@|  Off        | | |
     | | +-------------+  +------------+  +---------------+ | |
     | +----------------------------------------------------+ |
     | +----------------------------------------------------+ |
     | | @{" Start Dia   " Link DB }                     @{"   End Dia     " Link EB } | |
     | +----------------------------------------------------+ |
     +--------------------------------------------------------+
@endnode Using

@node Menu "The Menu Item's"

StartDia has 5 menu items:

About...    (A)
Load Config (L)
Use  Config (U)
Save Config (S)
---------------
Quit...     (Q)

The About menu provides you with information on this program and its
author.

The Load Config menu allows you to load a pre-saved config.  It will
be loaded from ENV:DiaStart.config.

The Use Config menu will save that current set of preferences to the
ENV:DiaStart.config file so they will be used until the Amiga looses
power or is switched of.

The Save Config menu will save that current set to both ENV:DiaStart
.config as well as ENVARC:DiaStart,config.  So these will become the
defacto settings until changes and re-saved.

The Quit menu will end StartDia. And if there is still a Dia running
that has been launched from StartDia, the user will be asked if that
program should be ended to.

Configuration items:

The ScreenDepth        (1,2,4,8,16,24)
The AutoClear setting. (On/Off)
The Zoom setting       (On/Off)
The Dia Path           (eg. egs:Piccolo/Dia/Dia)   

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode Menu

@node SB "ScreenMode Button"
 
SCREEN Button.
When clicking on the 'Screen' button you are presented with the ASL
(or ReqTools.) ScreenMode requester where you can select the screen
mode your wish Dia to use. If Dia has already been started by Start
Dia, it will be stopped, and restarted in the newly selected screen
mode.  Please note: The settings for Depth, Zoom and AutoClear will
be used. So make sure you first set these to the desired values.

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode SB

@node ST "ScreenMode Textgadget"
 
SCREEN Textgadget.
Here the selected screenmode name is displayed.

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode ST

@node QB "? Button"
 
? Button.
When clicking on this button you are presented with a requester that
shows you the current screenmode and the related Mode-ID in both HEX
and DEC format.

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode QB

@node FB "File Button"
 
FILE Button.
When you click on this button the ASL Filerequester will come up and
you can select a picture or anim you want Dia to display.  If Dia is
already running, it will load and display the anim/picture. If it is
not, you may start Dia by hitting the 'Start Dia' gadget.  The path,
pattern and filename you inputted will be remembered and used on the
subsequent calls to the filerequester.

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode FB

@node FT "File Textgadget"
 
FILE Textgadget.
Here the currently selected file is displayed.

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode FT

@node PB "Dia Path Button"
 
DIA PATH Button.
Here you can set the full path to where the Dia program can be found
on your system. this is typically only needed when you first use the
program. The information you input may be saved.

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode PB

@node PT "Dia Path Textgadget"
 
DIA PATH Textgadget.
Here the path and filename for the Dia program is displayed.

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode PT

@node RB "Rx Button"
 
RX Button.
When you press the button the 'ARexx Command' window opens. Here you
can select an ARexx command from the ListView and optionally add one
or more parameters in the stringgadget.  When you hit the Return key
while in the stringgadget, the command will be sent to Dia.  You may
use the 'RX' command to execte an ARexx script. Like my ShowDia.rexx
or DiaSlide.rexx scripts.    

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode RB

@node DC "ScreenDepth Cyclegadget"
 
DEPTH Cyclegadget.
Here you can select the depth (in bits) for  the screen to be opened
in.  Please note that there is no check made by StartDia to see if a
selected Screen can actually be as deep as specified.  

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode DC

@node ZC "Zoom Cyclegadget"
 
ZOOM Cyclegadget.
Here you xan specify if you wish the Dia Command Window to be Zoomed
(iconified) or not. 

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode ZC

@node AC "AutoClear Cyclegadget"
 
AUTOCLEAR Cyclegadget.
This gadget allows you to specify if before loading any picture file
the screen should be cleared of any already displayed pictures. 

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode AC

@node DB "Start Dia Button"
 
START DIA Button.
When you hit this one, Dia will be started using the parameters that
you have set for Screen Mode, File, Dia Path, AutoClear, ScreenDepth
and Zoom. 

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode DB

@node EB "End Dia Button"
 
END DIA Button.
Use this to end Dia. Although when you exit StartDia and a Dia thats
started form StartDia is still running, this program will ask you if
you wish to have it quit.

                     @{"Back to Window" Link Using }

@endnode EB


@node Misc_Info "Miscellaneous"

                          Miscellaneous

I spend quite a lot of time and effort on StartDia. And since I'm in
desperate need of some more memory and lacking sufficient funds I've
decided to make StartDia Shareware.  However, since I do not believe
in CrippleWare and trust the judgement of my fellow EGS users I have
not crippled this evaluation version in any way. Furthermore has the
contribution been set to a very modest sum of: US$5 / Fl.10 / DM 10.
(take your pick, whichever is best for you. I can handle all three.)

What do you get when you send in your contribution?

1. My appreciation for your contribution.

2. The knowledge that you have helped motivate me to keep up further
   development of this program, and possibly  similar ones for other
   applications.

3. The knowledge that if you like an enhancement or addition to this
   program, you will have my willing ear.  

That is about all you get for your money. Remember that old proverb:

              It's better to give than to recieve...

Well, I've given you StartDia, so it's your turn to give now. :-)
 
                              Feedback?

If you have questions or suggestion, bug reports or enhancements you
would like to see, please send these to:

